<p><b>Christian existentialism</b> describes a group of writings that take a philosophically <a href="/wiki/Existentialist" title="Existentialist" class="mw-redirect">existentialist</a> approach to Christian theology. The school of thought is often traced back to the work of <a href="/wiki/Denmark" title="Denmark">Danish</a> philosopher <a href="/wiki/S%C3%B8ren_Kierkegaard" title="Søren Kierkegaard">Søren Kierkegaard</a> (1813-1855).<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since January 2008" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup></p>
